If you have an attachment located on a page where the page title is something like {noformat}Attachments go -- here{noformat} when you try to include the attachment on another page you get an error, "Unable to render embedded object: File (myattachment.jpg) not found.  The following markup fails:
{noformat}
!Attachments go -- here^myattachment.jpg!
{noformat}

The workaround is the rename the source page, removing the double dash or changing it to a single dash and updating the link as necessary.

