When using JIRA Portlet macro within section macro causes "undefined" error in FireFox. This problem occurs in Confluence 2.10.x but not in Confluence 3.0.x

IE7 seems to be working. 

To reproduce this problem copy the following codes to a wiki page. 

{code}
{section}
{jiraportlet:anonymous=true|url=http://jira.atlassian.com/secure/RunPortlet.jspa?portletKey=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.portlets:projectstats&description=Stats:%20Confluence%20(Versions)&projectid=10470&statistictype=fixfor&template=/portlets/dashboard/projectstats.jsp}
{section}
{code}

A weblink in the body of a News item which renders correctly when the news item is viewed directly, is not rendered when the news item is shown in a panel macro using this markup:

{code}
{panel:title=Divisional News & Announcements|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#6699ff|titleBGColor=#D5EFFF|bgColor=#ffffff}
{blog-posts:1|content=excerpts|spaces=divrsrcs}[View all News Items|https://coral.uchicago.edu:8443/pages/viewrecentblogposts.action?key=divrsrcs] [Add a News Item|https://coral.uchicago.edu:8443/pages/createblogpost.action?spaceKey=divrsrcs]
{panel}
{code}

The panel macro displays the content like this:

We recently upgraded our wiki software to a new version. Many of you are already actively using the wiki to create content for a new departmental website. Some departments are also using the wiki to share information with their own faculty, students and staff.

For an overview of the new features in the latest version of the wiki software, please see the [current release notes|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+3. ...

Read more...

Here is a link to the page on which this appears: https://coral.uchicago.edu:8443/display/divrsrcs/Home

I've attached two screenshots to illustrate the correct and false rendering. I'm pretty sure this affected at least some versions prior to 3.0 as well.

